    <!--
        The scanning methods which specify the order in which the user wants the views to be
        traversed/highlighted. So for example, if the user chooses row/column scanning, all the
        views in a certain row are highlighted and scanning moves from the top row to the bottom
        row. Once a row is selected, the views in that row are scanned one after the other in
        a linear fashion.
    -->
    <string-array translatable="true" name="switch_access_scanning_methods_entries">
        <!--
            Linear scanning is a method that the user chooses to indicate how the views in a
            window should be highlighted/traversed. In linear scanning the highlighting of views
            moves from left to right, presenting one item at a time.

            Row/Column scanning is a method that the user chooses to indicate how the views in a
            window should be highlighted/traversed. In row/column scanning all the views in a
            certain row are highlighted and scanning moves from the top row to the bottom row. Once
            a row is selected, the views in that row are scanned one after the other.

            This option uses row-column scanning for keyboards, but linear scanning the rest of
            the time.
         -->
        <item>Linear scanning</item>
        <!--
            See previous item for context. This choice uses row-column scanning everywhere
         -->
        <item>Row-column</item>
        <!--
            Option scanning is a method that the user chooses to indicate how the views in a
            window should be highlighted/traversed. In option scanning the views are highlighted
            in groups. The user presses a button to choose a group. The options in the selected
            group are then divided into new groups. Eventually there's just one option that the
            user chooses.
         -->
        <item>Group selection</item>

        <!--
            Nomon clocks is a method that the user chooses to indicate how the views in a window
            should be highlighted/traversed. With Nomon clocks each actionable item on the screen
            has an animated clock next to it. The user presses a button when the rotating hand on
            the clock that corresponds to the desired actionable item on the screen enters the dark
            wedge at the top of the clock. Once the user presses the button, only the clocks still
            in a valid angle range will keep animating. User continues pressing the switch until
            their desired actionable item on the screen is selected.
        -->
        <item>Nomon Clocks</item>

    </string-array>

